el-Rufai, Lalong, Bagudu, Badaru Salute Kaduna Deputy Gov. On Her 54th Birthda By AZA MSUE, Kaduna Kaduna State Governor Nasir El-Rufai and his counterparts from Plateau, Kebbi and Jigawa states have felicitated with El-Rufai’s deputy, Dr. Hadiza Balarabe on her 54th birthday. They described Dr. Hadiza, who turned 54th on Wednesday 26 August, as a dedicated woman whose leadership qualities and dedication to public service are commendable. The governors salute Dr. Hadiza when they paid a visit to Governor Nasir El-Ruafi in Kaduna to commiserate with the government and people of the state over the resurgence of violent conflicts in some communities of Southern Kaduna and general security challenges in parts of the state that recently claimed many lives and property. Plateau state governor and chairman of Northern Governor’s Forum, Simon Lalong, said the forum has observed with delight the dedication and excellent support Dr. Hadiza is given governor El-Rufai in running the affairs of the state, saying the forum is proud of her outstanding performance, especially as the Chairman of the State Standing Committee on COVID-19. Lalong added that, commended Kaduna Deputy Governor steering the affairs of the state well when governor El-Rufai was in isolation treating coronavirus. Also speaking, Progressives Governors Forum Chairman and Kebbi State governor, Atiku Bagudu and his Jigawa counterpart, Mohammed Badaru Abubakar congratulated Dr. Hadiza on her 54th birthday, saying she is an inspiration to women, judging by her excellent leadership qualities. They all wished her long live and sound health. On his part, El-Rufai expressed confidence on his deputy, saying she is a woman of integrity who has dedicated herself to the service of the state and humanity.